Photo #MadeWithLightroom by @jcrrillo⁠
“Now Is All We’ve Got”⁠
⁠
This picture is dedicated to my friend Wesley, who is like a brother to me, he lived and went to Chico State University up in #NorthernCalifornia for six years. This last Spring, there were a lot of things happening at once so we took a trip to San Francisco to get away. We spent hours clearing our minds and deciding on what’s next. We often wondered if life would ever change, would we be successful someday? Is school even worth it? Wesley moved back home to Ventura, CA. I’m very proud of him for receiving his real estate license in Ventura County. After all of his hard work and dedication he figured out what he wanted to do and found his path.

Photo #MadeWithLightroom by @eyeofshe⁠
⁠
#DeathValley is one of those places that makes you question what planet you’re on. After driving through the night for 5 hours straight, then sleeping for 1 hour to be up for sunrise, let’s just say that by the end of my road trip I was feeling pretty rough. But after the grueling journey, we took a space shuttle to #Mars and all was well and good in the world.

⁠
I went out to the #HuntingtonBeach pier one evening to catch the sunset and photograph some of the #surfers. I just  happened to get lucky that the swell was fairly heavy that day, which I’m assuming attracted highly skilled surfers! I caught this surfer absolutely shredding on these big waves. It was such an incredible experience to witness and capture.

Photo #MadeWithLightroom by @gboxcreative⁠
⁠
Escaping to #Harar.⁠
⁠
I’ve recently found that the best things in life happen unexpectedly. The best stories begin with “and, all of a sudden…”. The best #adventures are never planned as they turned out to be. This trip was just that, unplanned days of exploring a beautiful city full of surprises.⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Adobe Photoshop Lightroom on July 23, 2021 tagging @gboxcreative. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
Photo #MadeWithLightroom by @gboxcreative⁠
⁠
Escaping to Harar.⁠
⁠
Harar (ሐረር), is a city in eastern Ethiopia. I had been there once before but never got the chance to photograph it. The colors, the people, and the old architecture stayed with me, so I always wanted to go back to photograph it.⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Adobe Photoshop Lightroom on July 21, 2021 tagging @stuffedbox. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text:
Photo #MadeWithLightroom by @stuffedbox⁠
⁠
A Keke (tricycle) driver waits for his turn at a bus stop in Dawaki, Abuja. It is a common tradition for them to have turns while they wait for passengers to arrive. Sometimes this takes ages and they take naps or move around and have discussions and laughs with their colleagues. ⁠

node.text:
Photo #MadeWithLightroom by @gboxcreative⁠
⁠
Escaping to Harar:⁠
I found myself in between wanting to escape my reality one minute and booking a plane ticket to one of the cities in Ethiopia that’s always fascinated me, Harar, the next minute. This image was the product of that, my trip to the beautiful city of Harar. ⁠
